---
import {
	MoonSat,
	SeaWaves,
	SigmaFunction,
	TemperatureDown,
} from 'iconoir-react';
---

<div class='space-y-6'>
	<p>
		Perhaps surprisingly, Neil is a <span class='text-xl text-red-500'
			>qualified physicist</span
		> 😯
	</p>
	<p>
		<MoonSat className='inline text-3xl text-zinc-600' /> He mainly uses his
		masters degree for:
	</p>
	<ul class='list-disc space-y-2 pl-6'>
		<li>
			talking about <span class='text-xl text-amber-600'>🍮 custard</span>
			more than is strictly necessary
		</li>
		<li>🤔 pub quizzes</li>
		<li>🗣️ winning arguments</li>
	</ul>
	<div class='text-center text-xl font-bold'>Unimportant Physics Facts:</div>
	<p>
		<SigmaFunction className='inline text-3xl text-zinc-600' /> Neil's favourite
		equation is: <span
			class='inline-block text-2xl text-blue-500 group-hover:animate-bounce-once'
			>Schrodinger</span
		>
	</p>
	<p>
		<TemperatureDown className='inline text-3xl text-zinc-600' /> Neil's least
		favourite physics: <span
			class='inline-block text-2xl text-orange-500 group-hover:animate-bounce-once'
			>Thermodynamics</span
		>
	</p>
	<p>
		<SeaWaves className='inline text-3xl text-zinc-600' /> This last fact is
		just: <span
			class='inline-block text-2xl text-purple-500 group-hover:animate-bounce-once'
			>an excuse to use the nice water wave icon</span
		>
	</p>
</div>
